"n. 长柄大锤 【英】 n.长柄大锤(a large heavy hammer that is wielded with both hands) 【记】 分割记忆：sledge(雪 橇)＋hammer(锤子) n. 长柄大锤(用于钉楔子、打桩和干重活) 【记】sledge(n 雪橇)＋hammer(n 锤) = 长柄大锤 【参】sledge(n 雪橇); = sleigh(n 雪撬) 【记】sledge sled 雪橇 + hammer 锤子，用来锻造雪橇的锤子 sledgehammer (n.)  late 15c., from sledge (n.1) + hammer (n.). As a verb, from 1834. Old English had slegebytel ""hammer,"" from beetle (n.2)."
